title: Frou Frou - Wikipedia
snippet: Frou Frou are an English electronic duo composed of musician and singer Imogen Heap and record producer Guy Sigsworth. They released their only studio album, Details, in 2002.

title: FROUFROU Definition & Meaning - Merriam-Webster
snippet: It later came to mean "ostentatious decoration," and its usage expanded beyond the world of fashion to other crafts such as architecture and interior design. These days it also shows up as the adjective frou-frou, meaning "very heavily decorated and fancy," as in "frou-frou designs."

title: FROU-FROU Definition & Meaning | Dictionary.com
snippet: FROU-FROU definition: elaborate decoration, as frills, ribbons, or ruffles, especially on women's clothing. See examples of frou-frou used in a sentence.

title: frou-frou - Wiktionary, the free dictionary
snippet: Jan 5, 2026 Â· Noun frou - frou (plural frou-frous) (onomatopoeia) A rustling sound, particularly the rustling of a large silk dress.

title: Frou-frou - Etymology, Origin & Meaning - Etymonline
snippet: Origin and history of frou-frou frou-frou (n.) 1870, "a rustling," from French (19c.), possibly imitative of the rustling of a dress. The word was popularized in English by a French play translated and given that name. Meaning "fussy details" is from 1876.
